The paper discusses the semantics of answer set programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves logical reasoning (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper may also be relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE) due to its focus on the equivalence property between two versions of the stable model semantics.
